# ============================================================
# EVENT CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: event
scope: event.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for event.

## policy_rules
Event policy constrains:
- which sources may emit events
- which payloads are allowed
- which events may be visible to which actors
- which events may be replayed or reprocessed
- how historical event data may be disclosed

## required_behavior
- source eligibility must be explicit
- payload allowance must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- replay allowance must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded public event summary
- actor-scoped event detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- replay/historical detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow event acceptance only for valid source scope
- allow payload only for declared meaning
- allow replay only for explicit replay mode
- deny hidden payload widening
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If source,
payload meaning,
replay scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the event path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- source policy is explicit
- replay policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
